'''戴维斯站'''（{{lang-en|Davis}}）位于[[马萨诸塞州|马萨诸塞州]][[萨默维尔_(马萨诸塞州)|萨默维尔]]市的{{tsl|en|Davis Square|戴维斯广场}}，是[[波士顿地铁红线|波士顿地铁红线]]地铁站。戴维斯站是萨莫维尔市仅有的两座地铁站之一，另外一座是[[波士顿地铁橙线|波士顿地铁橙线]]的[[组装厂站|组装厂站]]。

戴维斯站于1984年正式启用，其所在地戴维斯广场以1850年搬至此处的谷物经销商戴维斯（1819–1894）命名。<ref>{{cite web|date=December 2006 |url=http://community.livejournal.com/davis_square/744943.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120713161334/http://community.livejournal.com/davis_square/744943.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=July 13, 2012 |title=Rebekah Gewirtz E-Newsletter: December 2006 |accessdate=May 4, 2007 }}</ref>车站为无障碍车站，共建有两座地铁出入口、一座自行车停放点、公交车专用道和公交车终点站。

==历史==
[[File:Davis_station_under_construction,_1983.jpg|thumb]]
1858年之后，伴随着西萨默维尔社区的繁荣发展，有轨电车也在当地逐渐兴起，客运列车线路也十分流行。1870年开始，{{tsl|en|Boston and Lowell Railroad|波士顿和洛厄尔铁路}}上行驶的{{tsl|en|Lexington and West Cambridge Railroad|列克星敦和西剑桥铁路|列克星敦至阿灵顿线}}在戴维斯广场停靠，命名为'''西萨默维尔站'''（{{lang-en|West Somerville}}），1888年正式兴建车站。<ref name=biketour>[http://www.somervillema.gov/sites/default/files/May2008-HistoricBikeTourOfHistoriProposedGreenLineExtRailways.pdf "Rails of the Past" (2008), p. 6] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131215052424/http://www.somervillema.gov/sites/default/files/May2008-HistoricBikeTourOfHistoriProposedGreenLineExtRailways.pdf |date=December 15, 2013 }} Accessed December 15, 2013</ref>火车和有轨电车服务大大刺激了当地的发展，使戴维斯广场成为19世纪70至80年代当地重要的商业中心，90年代周围兴建了大量住宅区。<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.somervillema.gov/sites/default/files/documents/DavisToPowderHouseWalkingTour.pdf |title= College Avenue, Gateway to West Somerville – From Davis Square to the Medford Line |last1= Gordon |first1= Edward |date= Fall 2006 |website= somervillema,org |publisher= Chapter of Victoria Society of America |accessdate= December 7, 2013 |url-status= dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20131213064543/http://www.somervillema.gov/sites/default/files/documents/DavisToPowderHouseWalkingTour.pdf |archivedate= December 13, 2013 }}</ref>

1927年，铁路线改变线路，废弃的车站在1938年7月4日的大火中烧毁。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/36818799/the_boston_globe/ |title=Somerville Crowd Battles Firemen |date=July 5, 1938 |newspaper=Boston Globe |page=2 |via=Newspapers.com |accessdate=2020-09-11 |archive-date=2019-10-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191006202831/https://www.newspapers.com/clip/36818799/the_boston_globe/ |dead-url=no }} {{open access}}</ref>20世纪60至70年代，当地官员和居民成功说服[[马萨诸塞湾交通局|马萨诸塞湾交通局]]在戴维斯广场设立红线地铁站，并于1984年12月8日正式启用，<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wickedlocal.com/somerville/news/x1716633094/Column-Davis-Square-design-in-Somerville-will-be-community-driven |title=Column: Davis Square design in Somerville will be community-driven |last1=Curtatone |first1=Joe |last2=Gewirtz |first2=Rebekah |date=June 7, 2013 |publisher=Wicked Local Somerville |accessdate=December 7, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131213075235/http://www.wickedlocal.com/somerville/news/x1716633094/Column-Davis-Square-design-in-Somerville-will-be-community-driven |archivedate=December 13, 2013 }}</ref>这也大大振兴当地经济，促进周边地区发展。车站与波特站一样，在设计时按照无障碍车站设计，无需进行后期改造。<ref name=bluebook1990>{{cite web |url=https://archive.org/details/ridershipservice990mass |edition=3 |title=Ridership and Service Statistics |date=November 1990 |page=1-4 |publisher=Massachusetts Bay Transportation Authority |author=Operations Directorate Planning Division |via=Internet Archive}}</ref><ref name=2007doc>{{cite web |url=https://old.mbta.com/uploadedFiles/Accessibility/final%20report%20082407%20on%20CD.pdf |title=Evaluation of MBTA Paratransit and Accessible Fixed Route Transit Services: Final Report |publisher=Massachusetts Bay Transportation Authority |author=Tran Systems and Planners Collaborative |date=August 24, 2007 |access-date=2020-09-11 |archive-date=2019-11-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191130025704/https://old.mbta.com/uploadedFiles/Accessibility/final%20report%20082407%20on%20CD.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>

1993年6月，盲人玛格丽特·麦卡锡跌落站台，并被第三轨道上的高压电电击死亡，这起事故导致马萨诸塞湾交通局为所有地铁站站台安装[[导盲砖|导盲砖]]。<ref name=durso>{{cite thesis |url=https://dspace.mit.edu/handle/1721.1/66801 |title=Subway Spaces as Public Places: Politics and Perceptions of Boston's T |last=Durso |first=Holly Bellocchio |date=June 2011 |publisher=Massachusetts Institute of Technology |type=MCP |pages=37–38 |access-date=2020-09-11 |archive-date=2015-09-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150921183341/http://dspace.mit.edu/handle/1721.1/66801 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

马萨诸塞湾交通局计划为车站新增四座电梯和新一个新的夹层过道，并于2020年4月与施工方签署合约。<ref>{{cite web |url=https://cdn.mbta.com/sites/default/files/2020-04/2020-04-13-fmcb-19-architectural-engineering-services-station-accessibility-improvements-accessible.pdf |title=MBTA Contract Nos. A90PS02, A90PS04, & A90PS05: Architectural and Engineering Services for Station and Accessibility Improvements |first=John |last=Schwarz |date=April 13, 2020 |publisher=Massachusetts Bay Transportation Authority |access-date=2020-09-11 |archive-date=2021-12-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211202165540/https://cdn.mbta.com/sites/default/files/2020-04/2020-04-13-fmcb-19-architectural-engineering-services-station-accessibility-improvements-accessible.pdf }}</ref>

